Corne QMK workflow (programmatic)

1) Bootstrap tools and local qmk_firmware checkout
   kbd-setup

2) Edit keymap source
   - ~/.config/keyboard/corne-qmk/keymaps/ezra_corne/keymap.c

3) Sync source into qmk_firmware
   kbd-sync
   - Also regenerates layout images
   - Also reloads HUD overlay

4) Build UF2 for your RP2040 ProMicro Corne rev1
   kbd-build-all
   - Optional artifact variants:
     - kbd-build-left
     - kbd-build-right

5) Flash
   - For correct split handedness, use split flash targets (recommended):
     - mise run kbd_flash_left
     - mise run kbd_flash_right
   - Or direct commands:
     - kbd-flash-left
     - kbd-flash-right
   - During per-half flashing, disconnect TRRS between halves.
   - Enter bootloader on the half you are flashing (double-tap reset).
   - The board should reboot automatically after flash.
   - Left/right artifact files from `kbd-build-left/right` are convenience outputs and
     are not the authoritative handedness path.

6) Layout images and HUD
   - Images are generated automatically on kbd-sync/kbd-build/kbd-build-all
   - Manual regenerate: kbd-layout-images
   - Output path: ~/.config/keyboard/corne-qmk/images/generated/
   - Layer images: layer0.png layer1.png layer2.png
   - HUD reload: kbd-hud-reload

7) Keep source keymap authoritative
   - Main source: ~/.config/keyboard/corne-qmk/keymaps/ezra_corne/
